post_text:
THIS WAS EMAILED TO ALL INCOMING HS STUDENTS DIRECTLY ON THEIR SCHOOL EMAIL ACCOUNTS. IF YOU ARE A PARENT OF A INCOMING 9-12TH GRADER PLEASE HAVE THEM RESPOND IF INTERESTED.

Good afternoon,
I am reaching out because I want to address any concerns or questions anyone may have regarding the reopening of school. We have been working to prepare for our hybrid learning and addressing all the reopening guidelines we must follow to get you back in school. We are most concerned about providing the safest situation for everyone. Your opinion is important to me and I want to ease any anxiety and clarify what we must do to make this a smooth transition back to school. I also know you may have ideas or thoughts that could help us meet your needs.
I am planning to host a meeting (most likely virtual) for all 9th-12th grade students who are interested. If you are, please reply back to let me know . Once I hear from you, I will arrange a date and time.
Hope you are all enjoying your summer! Be well!

Mr. Thode

Today was phase two of Center Moriches Virtual Graduation prep. Nothing like what we hoped for and not the best way for SENIORS to be celebrated but here is a beautiful picture of two students loaded with pride, potential and appreciation. The photo is really a great symbol of our youth moving on in life. I was honored to walk 130 plus students through their photos and videos today. Each one of them is a beacon of hope for our future. God Bless Them All! I couldnt be prouder.

Class of 2020
